Slay Undead 3 and Holy steed, which would use up all my class points.  After thinking about it however, I think those 9 points spent to get Slay 3 would be better spent elsewhere in class skills.   The only reason I want slay undead is to get the oooh's and ahhh's of getting those huge slay crits.<br><br>Im trying to decide exactly what path I should take.   I still want holy steed, and at least slay undead 1, but from there I face my dilema.   What other AA skills should I choose from class?   I have to keep the points spent under 24 to retain my title.  If I go the slay1 and holysteed route, ill  have 15 more points to spend on other class skills.  If I go slay 2 and holy steed ill have 9 points to spend on other class skills.<br><br>Im looking for recomendations from people on what I should do.  Should I go with my original decision, or should I not go for slay 3 and use those aditional points for something else.   If so, what do you think I should use them on?<br><br>As a bit of background, My guild currently does not do north TOV or any encounters of similar difficulty.   We do have the firepower to take down mobs like Vindi, and perhaps Tormax in the near future though.   We will eventually move to NTOV after we have done enough quests in the halls of testing, and skyshrine.  <br><br>What should I do?  Suggestions, comments?<br><br><br><br>Sir Derek Drygon<br>59th rank Knight of Truth<br>Champions of Norrath<br>The Rathe <p>"Hear it not Heaven thine ministers have done it!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukropotkinnobleblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kropotkin Nobleblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 318<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 11:40:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14753.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://w3.one.net/~hodosko/images/ForwardKnightMarbleBkgd.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA point recomendation</span><hr size=1> Bah, keep getting AA points.   Personally I always use &quot;/shownames 1&quot;  so I never see anybodys title or even surname and guild.<br> <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=33435"><I><B>Kropotkin Nobleblade</a></I></B><BR>Crusader - <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern">The Nameless</a><BR><a href="http://www.valorguard.net">Valorguard</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirderekdrygon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Derek Drygon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 1:01:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14753.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://champions.morpheus.net/pics/derek2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA point recomendation</span><hr size=1> You may use that, but it doesnt prevent others from seeing your title.   Through every game I have ever played (even back in the old D&amp;D days) my paladin has been &quot;Sir Derek Drygon&quot;   Even before the AA titles came out, I called myself &quot;Sir Derek&quot;.  I would really like to keep this title and no ammount of persuading is going to convince me otherwise.  I just have to use my points more wisely then most people since I have a limit to the number I can use in class.<br><br>Until Verant gives us the option of choosing the title we want, which I doubt will ever happen, im going to stay under 23 class points.<br><br><br><br>Sir Derek Drygon <p>"Hear it not Heaven thine ministers have done it!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 1:05:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14753.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA point recomendation</span><hr size=1> I would just look at the class abilities that add strong value and those that do not and pick from there then.<br><br>Class skills I can get by without:<br><br>- act of valour, hard to time<br>- double riposte, level 3 will give you an increase of 2.5% if you get hit.<br>- divine stun, broken and does not work<br>- Body and Mind Rejuvenation, that is 10 point healing a minute and 10 extra mana per minute. Will make a little more efficient but not lots.<br>- fearless, at 59/60 the only time I might, and I say might get feared is gore, but only if we do not have a bard.<br>- mass group buff, I can hand buff a raid of 12 group in 2min. Not worth it, only if you are really lazy =p<br><br>Now to the ones that are atm good:<br><br>- 2h bash(6 points), 1% damage increase and useful during solos for runners/gaters/casters. Saves you tons of mana by using bash first before stun<br>- improved lay hands(5 points), soloing this might give you an extra k of healing, for raids can buy the CH chain 7-10 seconds to get their act together.<br>- physical enhancement(5 points), maybe 60 more hp and 2% more damage avoidange/mitigation (Great value for only 5 points)<br>- slay undead (3/6/9 points)<br><br>So you have 18 points to spend after the horse:<br><br>Solo oriented: slay undead 3 if you really want to live in undead dungeons/places forever =p = 18<br>Raid: lay hands(5), slay 2(9), act of valor(filler) or<br>        lay hands(5), physical enhancement(5), bash(6) = 16<br><br>Problem really is that it is hard to use up just 18 points. If you really want to get the best out of it, then buy a 100k horse. Then you can do the following<br><br>solo: (lay hands(5) or physical enhancement(5)) and slay3(18 )  <br>raid: lay hands(5), slay2(9), bash(6), act of valor(filler) or<br>raid: lay hands(5), slay1(3), bash(6), physical enhancement(5), act of valor(3, to fill)<br><br>In my opinion I would just give up on slay undead if you want the best raid setup and still get the horse:<br><br>lay hands(5), bash(6), phsical enhancement(5), horse(5)<br><br>No matter what you pick you will be short 2 points or have to fill with act of valor/double riposte.<br><br>I personally might go for the lay hand/bash/slay undead(2)/horse route, then fill up arch skills and then continue on class.<br><br><br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A> at: 3/7/02 1:10:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucaladel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 2:24:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14753.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA point recomendation</span><hr size=1> If you really are set on only doing 23 or less points in class, id agree with giving up the horse, you can buy one that is close(you lose the instacast and the cr potential). That gives you a few more points to spend.<br><br>I personally put off getting duke till i had near 60 points; i wanted to keep sir as well, but fuq it getting slay 3 was more fun, not like i stare at the title over my head all the time anyway.<br><br>If you had to limit it, mabye do: slay 2, bash, physical enhancement, that leaves 3 so either double ripost lvl 1 or act of valor both equally useless, and buy a white horse instead.<br><br>or if buying the horse is outa the question: slay 1, 2h bash, physical enhance, holy steed, that leaves 4 so either act of valor or ripost 1 again. Tho you might be unhappy with the low frequency of slay 1.<br><br>If you are more raid orenited then exp/doing your own thing, mabye do improved loh over PE.<br><br>It really matters what you find useful tho...<br><br>My opinion is something like this....<br><br>Slay is fun; but only useful against undead of while probably about 5-10% of the entire games content is. 2h  Still a game is about havig fun, and this really is a defining skill.<br><br>Bash is really useful, not being able to bash with a 2hander is a big hindrance, it wont add much to your damage output, mabye arround 2-3%; but invaluable for moving npcs(this can be good or bad) and inturrupting npcs.<br><br>Act of valor, im sure this one will not be missed.<br><br>Mass group buff, im sure this one will not be missed. With brells you can buff a raid of 50 in about 2 minutes, using mabye half mana, so its no big deal.<br><br>Holy steed, fun skill, but you can buy a horse, and its utility is limited. Mainly good for cr. There are still a few minor advantages to using a horse while doing certain things. And there is still one combat advantage(or disadvantage depending how you look at it) to fighting on a horse, but god is combat on horseback annoying.<br><br>Physical Enhancement will provide a decent boost to your skills, its useful.<br><br>Divine stun, currently its broken, but assuming its fixed to its description, it will be useful in some situations. but those situations will be few. Most end game stuff seems to be above 60, even the guards are above 60 so divine stun wouldnt work.<br><br>Body and mind rejuv, not a bad skill but its prereqs are high; if you meet the prereqs you should get the skill, but it probably wouldnt be very missed.<br><br>Fearless, i dont think you will miss this one, limited usefullness. Few encounters would require it by the level you get it, most encounters of that level have weak fear or no fear, a few have strong fear....but those few are also quite easily mastered these days....in the grand scheme of things anyway.<br><br>Double riposte, not a bad skill, but limited damage iincrease, and again only if you tank...you probably wont miss this one either.<br><br>Improved lay on hands, well first the solo potential. If you use loh the second it pops and get full life from it thats the equiv of 3.5hp regened a tic. So, improving loh and considering you get 4000 useful outa it, thats like another 2hp a tic. Most people probably wont get 4k outa an loh while soloing, unless they are using buffs, but the additional mana cost of the buffs would negate the extra effect of the loh....so for soloing it wont help all that much, in terms of efficancy anyway. Now for raids, there are instances where loh helps a lot, it can be hard at times to know when to use it and when to not, but here improved loh would mean much more, doubling the effect or trippling the effect of your current loh. This one might or might not be missed, it can be handy tho. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=14753.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=14753.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14753.topic&index=4><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=14753.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=14753.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14753.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14753.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm14">Old World<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm15">New World<option value="paladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests">Holy Quests<option 